## Summary

The C4 analysis yielded an aggregated total of {{ report.high_count }} unique
vulnerabilities. Of these vulnerabilities, {{ report.high_count }} received a
risk rating in the category of HIGH severity and {{ report.medium_count }}
received a risk rating in the category of MEDIUM severity.

Additionally, C4 analysis included {{ report.qa_count }} reports detailing issues
with a risk rating of LOW severity or non-critical. There were also
{{ report.gas_count }} reports recommending gas optimizations.

All of the issues presented here are linked back to their original finding.

## Scope

The code under review can be found within the [C4 {{ report.title }} repository](https://github.com/code-423n4/{{ report.slug }}), and is composed of {{ report.sloc_count }} smart contracts written in the Solidity programming language and includes {{ report.sloc }} lines of Solidity code.

## Severity Criteria

C4 assesses the severity of disclosed vulnerabilities based on three primary
risk categories: high, medium, and low/non-critical.

High-level considerations for vulnerabilities span the following key areas
when conducting assessments:

- Malicious Input Handling
- Escalation of privileges
- Arithmetic
- Gas use

For more information regarding the severity criteria refer to the
documentation found in our [judging documentation](https://docs.code4rena.com/awarding/judging-criteria/severity-categorization).

